# Operating model

- Read `AGENTS.md` before making changes.
- Work from an explicit outcome and keep the diff to the smallest coherent change.
- Inspect adjacent code before choosing a pattern; prefer reuse over parallel implementations.
- Plan before editing when a change crosses files, concerns, or approval boundaries.
- Run only documented project commands and report their actual results.
- Do not add dependencies, change services, weaken checks, deploy, or modify production settings without approval.
- Stop when required copy, claims, design direction, privacy decisions, or acceptance criteria are missing.
- Return evidence: changed files, checks, results, risks, and manual review needs.
